this could be done globally in a pytest autouse fixture as setup or teardown.
And the fixture can be used in tests to get the langchain_text_splitters module
```python
@pytest.fixture(autouse=True)
def langchain_text_splitters() -> ModuleType:
    """Force-reimport langchain_text_splitters from scratch."""
    to_remove = [
        key
        for key in sys.modules
        if key == "langchain_text_splitters"
        or key.startswith("langchain_text_splitters.")
    ]
    for key in to_remove:
        del sys.modules[key]
    return importlib.import_module("langchain_text_splitters")
```

